/Composer, out/

...
If you have some you want to share, from the way-down-deep place, please share it. I want to 'be' with it...
...even if you've never written two notes before or you share it via playing or writing etc...

...
That's okay. 
I just wanted to say that I think you all have something beautiful in there, and I'd love to hear it...
...I know some will agree, some will disagree, most will be like " this is the internet, I come here for the cats"...
...The game of being an artist has subverted the being of being an artist...

...
I almost think the arts could use a tabla rasa. Start over. There's too much thinking in art and not enough 'being'....
I'm not talking personality, that's the nail polish. I'm talking deeper... Gullivers travels of the spirit type thing.

... will let the diamond sparkle through. 

Notions of good music be damned. I want to hear what's glittering deep down...
We're all diamonds covered in the mud of our thinking, with some glossy nail polish on top to hide it. No amount of nail polish...

... sharing your soul with a lover or
 close friend? I want to hear that vulnerability in music. The openness that shows a deeper humanness

..
Screw the whole "well, ideally you have both craft and spiritual outpouring". Do you need to speak in perfect sentences...
..pour out your soul, be totally vulnerable without the shelter of conceptual ideas?...
...I mean, cool, that's nice, but can you set that aside and sing your blues? Pour out your soul, be totally vulnerable...

...singing their own 'blues' (spiritual outpouring).

I don't really care if you're the world's best orchestrator or craftsman....

...
I want genuine, unassuming, unapologetic, earnestness. I don't want schools or styles, but every Composer an unschooled barbarian...
the assumed roles composers play out, but music as an intimate reflection of a composer's being. Messy, rambling, etc are all welcome...
I wish the ideas of good music, technique, structure, craft etc were forgotten so that we can hear not the learned ideas or...
